India Equities: Jaiprakash Power, Mahindra Composite, Unitech

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-02-15T04:33:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/coal-india-reliance-communications-india-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 10:01 a.m. local time.    India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
fell 58.49, or 0.3 percent, to 18,143.71.  Amtek India Ltd. (AMTK IN) rose 2.9 percent to 121.65
rupees, headed for highest close since Jan. 28. The auto-parts
maker reported a 22 percent rise in third-quarter net income
from a year earlier.    Jaiprakash Power Ventures Ltd . (JPVL IN) jumped 4.7 percent
to 42.65 rupees. The company plans to raise 35 billion rupees
($771 million) from global depository receipts or a follow-on
public share sale, Chairman Manoj Gaur said.    Jubilant Life Sciences Ltd . (JOL IN) declined 4.6 percent
to 192 rupees, set for its lowest close since July 2009. The
drug and chemicals maker plans to borrow $202 million to redeem
convertible bonds maturing in May, Executive Director R.
Sankaraiah said in a conference call.    Mahindra Composites Ltd . (MCOM IN) advanced 3.7 percent to
63.95 rupees, headed for best close since Jan. 31. The company
approved the issue of shares to existing shareholders on a
rights basis, the company said in a statement to the Bombay
Stock Exchange.    Parsvnath Developers Ltd . (PARSV IN) added 2.4 percent to
29.6 rupees. The New Delhi-based builder of townships and
industrial parks reported a 26 percent rise in net income for
the third quarter ended December from a year earlier.    Unitech Ltd . (UT IN) fell 5.1 percent to 34.40 rupees, set
for its worst close in almost 25 months. India’s second-biggest
developer by assets posted a 37 percent slide in third-quarter
profit from a year earlier to 1.11 billion rupees as sales
declined, according to its statement to the Bombay Stock
Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
